            <div class="text-[#3A403A] space-y-5">
                <p class="text-xl font-bold border-l-4 border-[#82998A] pl-3">
                    Project Summary: State Management in Real-Time
                </p>
                <p>
                    **Pixel Pet Adventures** is a cute virtual pet simulator focused on modern **object-oriented design** principles in JavaScript. The game manages the pet's core state (hunger, happiness, sleep) which degrades over time.
                </p>
                <p>
                    A key challenge of this project was implementing state persistence. The game uses **HTML5 Local Storage** to save the pet's condition every few seconds. When the player returns, the game calculates the time elapsed and updates the pet's stats, simulating continuous, real-time progression even when the browser is closed. This was an excellent exercise in practical data management.
                </p>
                
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold pt-4 text-[#82998A]">Key Technologies & Skills Demonstrated</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2 text-lg">
                    <li>**Language:** JavaScript üíª (Used for core logic and DOM manipulation)</li>
                    <li>**Front-end:** HTML5 and minimal CSS3.</li>
                    <li>**Persistence:** Local Storage for persistent, real-time state management.</li>
                    <li>**Code Practice:** Clear class hierarchy for the Pet object and its behaviors.</li>
                </ul>

